<F P=100> West Europe </F>
<H3> <TI>   Li Ruihuan Meets Swedish Foreign Trade Minister </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Li Ruihuan Meets Swedish Foreign Trade Minister </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1405152494 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 0120 
GMT 11 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW1405152494 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Chinese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By reporter Xu Furui (6079 4395 3843)] </F>
  [Text] Stockholm, 10 May (XINHUA) -- Li Ruihuan, chairman 
of the National Committee of the Chinese People's Political 
Consultative Conference, met with Swedish Foreign Trade Minister 
Dinkelspiel here this afternoon. The two firmly believe that 
there are broad prospects for mutually beneficial economic 
cooperation and trade between China and Sweden. 
  Li Ruihuan said: Sweden is up to the world's highest 
standards in the fields of transport, telecommunications, 
energy, and medicine. Over the last decade and more, many 
Swedish enterprises have actively entered the market in China, 
and a number of new Sino- Swedish joint ventures are being set 
up. "We welcome more Swedish enterprises to take an active part 
in competition in the Chinese market. We are glad to see that 
the Swedish Government takes a positive attitude toward the 
development of Sino-Swedish economic relations and trade." 
  Dinkelspiel said: At present, Swedish enterprises are 
greatly interested in the Chinese market and both their trade 
volume and investment in China are increasing. The Swedish 
Government is making efforts to promote the economic cooperation 
and trade between the two countries. He said that the Swedish 
Government supports the restoration of China's signatory status 
in the GATT because it helps promote global trade and conforms 
to the interests of the Swedish people. 

</TEXT>

