<F P=100> NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political &amp; Social </F>
<H3> <TI>   Li Lanqing Addresses Vocational Education Meeting </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Li Lanqing Addresses Vocational Education Meeting </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1905103894 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 0711 
GMT 6 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW1905103894 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Chinese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By GUANGMING RIBAO reporter Zhang Yufu (1728 7183 4395) and </F>
XINHUA reporter Zhu Dongju (2612 0392 5468)] 
  [Excerpts] Beijing, 6 May (XINHUA) -- The 1994 national 
congress of China Vocational Education Service was held in 
Beijing today. On behalf of the CPC Central Committee and the 
State Council, Li Lanqing, member of the CPC Central Committee 
Political Bureau and vice premier of the State Council, attended 
the congress to offer congratulations and deliver a speech. 
  He said: Since its inception, China Vocational Education 
Service has devoted itself to researching and promoting 
vocational education, has set up various vocational schools, and 
has disseminated new ideas aimed at linking education with 
labor, such as those promoting "respect for labor," "manual 
skills," and the "application of both physical and mental 
power." This has helped nurture large numbers of specialized 
personnel who are knowledgeable and technically skilled. 
[passage omitted] 
  Li Lanqing noted: Educational development will determine 
whether we can build a socialist market economic system, and 
whether we can realize modernization; so will the improvement of 
national quality and the training of various specialized 
personnel. Our country is not an economically developed nation 
but it has to undertake the world's most extensive educational 
service; this is the reality of our education situation. By the 
end of this century, therefore, we should vigorously expand 
vocational education and train large numbers of people with 
practical skills needed for developing the socialist market 
economy, while basically universalizing the nine-year compulsory 
educational system, and basically eradicating illiteracy among 
youth. This provides the means by which we can achieve greater, 
faster, better, and more economical results in solving our 
country's educational problems; it can be described as a 
fundamental solution. The development of vocational education 
is a basic task of strategic importance for improving workers 
ideologically, morally, scientifically, and culturally, and for 
realizing socialist modernization; it is also of special 
importance to further consolidating the socialist system lead by 
the working class and based on the worker-peasant alliance. 
[passage omitted] 
  Attending today's opening ceremonies were Ni Zhifu, vice 
chairman of the National People's Congress Standing Committee; 
Ngapoi Ngawang Jigme and Wan Guoquan, vice chairmen of the 
National Committee of the Chinese People's Political 
Consultative Conference; and responsible persons from various 
democratic parties, the All-China Federation of Industry and 
Commerce, and relevant departments. 

</TEXT>

