<H3> <TI>   Li Ruihuan Continues Visit to European Countries </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Li Ruihuan Continues Visit to European Countries </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Leaves Denmark for Belgium </H4>

<F P=102> OW1905110294 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 1549 
GMT 17 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW1905110294 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Chinese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By reporter Xu Furui (6079 4395 3843)] </F>
  [Text] Copenhagen, 17 May (XINHUA) -- Li Ruihuan, chairman 
of the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference 
National Committee, wound up his four-day official goodwill 
visit to Denmark and left here for Belgium by special plane this 
afternoon. 
  He was sent off at the airport by Danish Foreign Ministry 
officials and Chinese Ambassador to Denmark Zheng Yaowen. 
  During his visit, Li Ruihuan held talks with Danish 
Government and parliament leaders, visited universities and 
industrial enterprises, met with entrepreneurs, and stayed at a 
farmhouse. The visit was a success. 
  It is understood that while departing Denmark, he cabled a 
telegram from the airplane to Danish Foreign Minister Petersen, 
thanking the Danish Government for the warm reception granted to 
him. He said: "I am convinced the strengthening of Sino-Danish 
friendship and cooperation accords with the interests of the two 
peoples." 

</TEXT>

