<F P=100> NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political &amp; Social </F>
<H3> <TI>   Security Ministry Trains Local Bureau Chiefs </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Security Ministry Trains Local Bureau Chiefs </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   HK1905152094 Beijing RENMIN RIBAO in Chinese 24 Apr 94 p 3 </F>
<F P=103> HK1905152094 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing RENMIN RIBAO </F>
<F P=105>  Chinese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By reporter Wang Bixue (3769 3024 1331): "Ministry of </F>
Public Security Trains Over 2,700 County, City Public Security 
Bureau Chiefs, Commissars in Past Three Years"] 
  [Text] Beijing, 23 Apr (RENMIN RIBAO)--This reporter 
learned from the Ministry of Public Security today that in order 
to improve the quality of the cadres who supervise grass-roots 
public security organs, and to meet the demand of public 
security work under the new situation of reform and opening up, 
since 1991, the Ministry of Public Security has offered training 
to chiefs and political commissars from county and city public 
security bureaus throughout the country, training 2,700 persons 
in three years. 
  Over the past few years, the Ministry of Public Security 
party committee has attached great importance to the training of 
chiefs and political commissars from county and city public 
security bureaus and has adopted a serious of effective 
measures: In 1992 and 1993, it organized seminars for chiefs of 
public security departments and bureaus, inspection tours for 
senior police officers, and study classes on learning from 
volume three of the Selected Works of Deng Xiaoping. Over the 
past three years, various public security departments and 
bureaus have also trained over 6,000 deputy chiefs and political 
commissars of county and city public security bureaus, and 
nearly 100,000 policemen of various arms of the police force 
have obtained on-the-job training certificates. Wang Zikang, 
director of the training and education section in the political 
department of the Ministry of Public Security, revealed that 
from now on, for every five-year period, the Ministry of Public 
Security will arrange training with different contents and 
duration according to changes in the situation and duties. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

