<F P=100> Economic &amp; Agricultural </F>
<H3> <TI>   State Assets Over 3000 Billion Yuan in 1992 </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    State Assets Over 3000 Billion Yuan in 1992 </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   HK1905112694 Beijing RENMIN RIBAO in Chinese 18 May 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> HK1905112694 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing RENMIN RIBAO </F>
<F P=105>  Chinese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By Li Jianxing (2621 1696 5281): "China's State-Owned </F>
Assets Exceed 3,000 Billion Yuan by End of 1992"] 
  [Text] Beijing, 17 May (RENMIN RIBAO)--The gross quantity 
of state assets in our country has increased rapidly in recent 
years, and they have also yielded better economic returns. 
According to statistics from the State Bureau for Management of 
State-Owned Assets, by the end of 1992, the gross book value of 
state assets in our country reached 3,069.7 billion yuan (not 
including resource-like assets and state assets held by the 
Armed Forces and the armed police force), and increased they had 
by 14.3 percent or 385.1 billion yuan over the previous year's 
figure of 2,684.6 billion yuan. 
  State assets managed by central institutions were worth 
1,458.4 billion yuan and accounted for 47.5 percent of the 
total, with state assets managed by localities worth 1,611.3 
billion yuan, accounting for 52.5 percent. In terms of use, 
state assets used in economic operations were worth 2,210.1 
billion yuan and accounted for 72 percent, while state assets 
not involved in economic operations were worth 859.6 billion 
yuan and accounted for 28 percent. State assets involved in 
economic operations increased by 13.1 percent, or 256.5 billion 
yuan, over the previous year. 
  Regarding the distribution of state assets in various 
trades, 
at the end of 1992, state assets in state-owned industrial 
enterprises throughout the country were worth 1,649.8 billion 
yuan. State-owned enterprises accounted for over 90 percent of 
all assets in such important industries as energy, 
transportation, mining, high technology, banking, and foreign 
trade industries. The gross quantity of state assets in the 
manufacturing industry, the construction and engineering 
industry, and agriculture, forestry, and water resources 
industries increased at a rate 10 percentage points higher than 
the national average growth rate. Assets in the real estate 
industry and enterprises adopting the joint-stock system 
increased at the highest rate. At the end of 1992, state assets 
in the real estate industry were worth 90.5 billion yuan, an 
increase of 69.8 percent over the previous year, and the gross 
quantity of state assets in enterprises that have adopted the 
joint-stock system reached 28.4 billion yuan, or an increase of 
175.7 percent over the previous year. The state-owned economy 
as a whole grew continuously and became the predominant force in 
the national economy [sentence as published]. 
  Through in-depth reform and expanded opening, state-owned 
enterprises continuously increased their dynamism and improved 
their economic results. 
  By the end of 1992, tax and profit contributions by 
state-owned enterprises throughout the country amounted to 329.1 
billion yuan, increasing by 45.3 billion yuan or 16 percent over 
the previous year. They earned 117.6 billion yuan of profits, 
an increase of 11.3 percent or 11.9 billion yuan over the 
previous year. Enterprises incurring losses accounted for 24.3 
percent of the total number of state-owned enterprises, down 7.3 
percentage points from the previous year's level of 31.6 
percent. The proportion of business losses in economic results 
declined to 26.7 percent from 32.1 percent in the previous year. 
Tax and profit contributions made by state-owned enterprises 
accounted for about two-thirds of the state's fiscal revenues. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

