<F P=100> Economic &amp; Agricultural </F>
<H3> <TI>   Enterprise Market Failure Leads to `Low' Efficiency </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Enterprise Market Failure Leads to `Low' Efficiency </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   HK1905112294 Beijing ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE in English 0942 GMT 
19 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK1905112294 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, May 19 (CNS) -- According to a research 
report recently published by the state Statistical Bureau of 
China, with the deepening of China's reform, failing to meet 
demand of market by Chinese enterprises has become the main 
factor conditioning their low economic efficiency. 
  The report said with the economic system reform got underway 
in an overall way and the implementation of those regulations 
concerned in recent years, adjustment of market force had played 
more and more important role. An investigation made by relevant 
departments in 1991 into loss-making 50 enterprises from 
Beijing, Shenyang and Tianjin had attributed the reason for loss 
of these enterprises to wrong policies, unfavourable 
circumstances and bad management, which made up 19.4 percent, 
47.8 percent and 32.8 percent of the total reason respectively. 
However, according to another investigation made in last year 
into more than 2500 loss-making enterprises from eight provinces 
and cities such as Shanghai, Shandong and Jilin, the ratios of 
the reason of wrong policies and unfavourable circumstances had 
dropped to 9 percent or so respectively and the ratio of the 
reason of bad management in these enterprises risen to about 82 
percent, indicating bad management and failure in meeting demand 
of market had become the main factor conditioning their economic 
efficiency. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

