<F P=100> Economic &amp; Agricultural </F>
<H3> <TI>   Economy Said Operating in `Yellow Light Zone' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Economy Said Operating in `Yellow Light Zone' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   HK1905143994 Beijing ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE in English 1144 GMT 
19 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK1905143994 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, May 19 (CNS)--According to a report from 
the State Statistical Bureau on operation of the national 
economy in China, the economic development in the country last 
month was stable and the macro economic situation was basically 
normal. The price growth, however, was still high, difficulties 
facing state-owned enterprises still existed and macro control 
and adjustment still needed to continue. 
  Last month saw an increase of investment in fixed assets and 
the investment structure was improved with fixed assets 
investment in last month increased by 44.2 percent over the same 
period last year and by 8 percentage points over the first three 
months this year. Investment in transportation continued to grow 
and that in machinery, light industry and construction of 
vocational villages and luxurious villas was curbed. The 
overall investment structure in the country turned for better 
than the same period last year. 
  The social retail value of consumer goods in last month 
increased by 24.3 percent over the same period last year. Last 
month saw a steady increase of financial revenue. In the first 
four months of this year, the growth of financial revenue was 
slightly bigger than that of financial expenditure, indicating a 
normal operation of reform for the financial and tax system in 
the country. 
  The added-value earned from industry in the country last 
month increased by 17.9 percent over the same period last year 
with growth being 2 percentage points higher than the average 
growth in the first quarter this year. Growth of export was 
faster than that of import for the first time since September 
1992. The state's surplus of foreign exchange continued to grow 
and the financial situation in the country was on the whole 
good. Despite large scale of purchasing treasure bonds in the 
country, residential savings deposits in last month increased by 
RMB 15.9 billion [renminbi], loans for agricultural and 
industrial purposes also increased and currency withdrawal from 
circulation continued. 
  Last month saw a 21.7 percent rise of prices of consumer 
goods in the country over the same period last year with the 
prices for grain, catering trade, fruits, clothing and service 
items increasing by a comparatively large scale. Prices for 
vegetables, however, declined. In the first four months, 
residential living costs increased by 22.2 percent over the same 
period of last year and commodity retail prices by 20 percent. 
In this period, profits earned and tax paid by state-owned 
enterprises grew at a relatively large scale but at the same 
time, loss made by loss-making enterprises also increased by 
62.6 percent and capital occupation rate by products by 13.8 
percent. [sentence as received] 
  It is predicted that the national economic operation in this 
month in the country will remain in the "yellow light" zone with 
various kinds of economic indices to be nearly the same last 
month. 

</TEXT>

