<F P=100> Economic &amp; Agricultural </F>
<H3> <TI>   XINHUA Carries Economic News Briefs for 20 May </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    XINHUA Carries Economic News Briefs for 20 May </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2005040594 Beijing XINHUA in English 0249 GMT 20 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2005040594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, may 20 (XINHUA) -- Today's economic news in 
brief. 
<H5>  New Air Route </H5>
  A Boeing 737 airliner concluded the first flight Tuesday [17 
May] on a new route from Mudanjiang, in northeast China's 
Heilongjiang Province, to Shanghai and Guangzhou. 
<H5>  Poverty Relief </H5>
  East Fujian's Saiqi economic development zone, the country's 
only poverty-relief project with foreign investment, is 
proceeding smoothly. 
  By now, 14 foreign-invested enterprises have been 
established 
in the zone, with 88 million yuan (about one million U.S. 
dollars) in total contracted investment. 
<H5>  Radio Paging Network </H5>
  China's first three-number radio paging network started 
operation Tuesday in 12 eastern coastal cities in Shandong, 
Zhejiang and Jiangsu provinces, and Shanghai. 

</TEXT>

