<F P=101> East Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Fujian Employs More Foreign Experts </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Fujian Employs More Foreign Experts </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2005073294 Beijing XINHUA in English 0726 GMT 20 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2005073294 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Fuzhou, May 20 (XINHUA) -- Southeast China's Fujian 
Province plans to employ 3,000 foreign experts to help with its 
economic development, while sending 5,000 of its own people 
abroad to take advanced training courses in the coming two years. 
  These people will be mainly involved in the fields of 
agriculture, industry, science and technology, and education. 
  One of the first provinces in China to carry out the reform 
and open further to the outside world, Fujian has long paid 
attention to inviting talented people, an official of the 
provincial bureau of personnel said. 
  A survey shows that 1,800 technicians, managerial workers 
and 
experts in culture and education from Japan, the United States, 
Germany, Italy, Denmark, and Taiwan and Hong Kong have been 
invited to work in the province since 1984. 

</TEXT>

