<F P=100> Central-South Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Price Increases Reportedly Slower in Guangzhou </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Price Increases Reportedly Slower in Guangzhou </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   HK1905145494 Guangzhou Guangdong People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 1000 GMT 13 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK1905145494 </F>
<F P=104>  Guangzhou Guangdong People's Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Mandarin </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Price hikes in the city of Guangzhou are slowing 
down somewhat. According to statistics, in April this year, the 
city's general level of retail prices and general level of 
wholesale prices were 17.5 and 21 percent higher respectively 
than the same period last year. However, compared with March 
this year, the margins of increase were 3.7 and 4.6 percent 
lower respectively. 
  The main reason why price hikes in April slowed somewhat is 
that the government has adopted relevant measures to curb price 
increases. 

</TEXT>

