<H3> <TI>   Guangdong's Zhuhai Eases Visa Requirements for Tourists </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Guangdong's Zhuhai Eases Visa Requirements for Tourists </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   HK1905145094 Beijing ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE in English 1403 GMT 
19 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK1905145094 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Zhuhai, May 19 (CNS) -- Zhuhai, the Special 
Economic Zone city in Guangdong Province, which was recently 
named "Tourism City" by the National Tourism Administration, has 
announced that foreign tourists holding unsigned visas are 
allowed to stay in the city within three days and this 
regulation will go into effect next month. 
  According to Mayor of Zhuhai, Mr. Liang Guangda, the above 
measure is aimed at further opening the city to the outside 
world and vitalizing tourism industry there and is an important 
step for the smooth implementation of exemption of visa for 
overseas visitors. 
  The city has seen a graudal increase of foreign tourists and 
the number of such tourists last year reached 60,000. With the 
implementation of the above measure, foreign visitors to the 
city this year are expected to be over one million. 

</TEXT>

