<H3> <TI>   Cities Along Yangtze Support Three Gorges Project </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cities Along Yangtze Support Three Gorges Project </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2005073694 Beijing XINHUA in English 0728 GMT 20 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2005073694 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Nanjing, May 20 (XINHUA) -- Cities in the valley of 
the Chang Jiang river fully support the construction of the 
Three Gorges water conservancy project. 
  The project, to be built on the middle reaches of this 
China's longest river, near Yichang city, Hubei Province, will 
have a generating capacity of 17.68 million kw upon completion. 
  Shanghai, on the Chang Jiang estuary, took the lead in 
encouraging its enterprises and organizations to set up economic 
entities around the construction site to offer more jobs for 
local people. 
  It also allocated special funds to help Yichang train 
technicians. 
  Wuhan, capital of Hubei Province, has completed 60 projects 
with a total investment of 83.47 million yuan in co-operation 
with Yichang city. 
  Located on the upper reaches of the Yangtze, Chongqing city 
in Sichuan Province has set up production bases for building 
materials and farm and sideline products specially geared to the 
construction of the Three Gorges project. 

</TEXT>

