<F P=100> North Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Longest Local Railway Completed in Inner Mongolia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Longest Local Railway Completed in Inner Mongolia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1905134394 Beijing XINHUA in English 1328 GMT 19 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1905134394 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Hohhot, May 19 (XINHUA) -- China's longest local 
railway -- from Jining to Tongliao in northern China's Inner 
Mongolia Autonomous Region -- has been completed after nearly 
four years of construction. 
  The 943-kilometer long railway, which cost 1.8 billion yuan, 
will greatly ease the middle and short-range passenger and 
freight transport pressure in northern China, officials from the 
Ministry of Railways said at a ceremony yesterday. 
  The railway will be an important route for passengers, coal 
and timber from the western part of the region to the eastern 
coast. Rich natural resources will be better utilized and 
development of minority nationalities-inhabited areas will be 
accelerated, officials said. 
  The railway will be a section of the second Eurasia railway, 
to run from Jinzhou city in Liaoning Province to Rotterdam in 
the Netherlands via Erenhot, Ulaanbataar and Moscow. 
  The new local railway is aimed to have an annual handling 
capacity of seven million tons in the near future and 17 million 
tons later. The track crosses four leagues (prefectures) and 13 
counties or banners. 
  The railway will cut 537 km off the route from the four 
leagues to Hohhot, capital of the autonomous region, compared 
with the old route via Hebei Province or Beijing. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

