<DOCNO> FBIS4-50718 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drchi098_r_94004" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-CHI-94-098 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  18 May 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> North Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Shanxi Applies Scientific Methods to Agriculture </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Shanxi Applies Scientific Methods to Agriculture </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1805095594 Beijing XINHUA in English 0921 GMT 18 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1805095594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Taiyuan, May 18 (XINHUA) -- Shanxi Province in north 
China has applied 332 scientific and technological achievements 
in agriculture over the past decade. 
  A local government official said that this scientific 
progress has resulted in increases of 20.29 billion kilograms of 
grain and 27.8 billion yuan in farmers' income over the past ten 
years. 
  The province has used more than 100 fine seeds in 3.2 
million 
hectares, an area which accounts for 80 percent of the total 
arable land in the province. 
  The Shanxi Academy of Agricultural Sciences, Shanxi 
University of Agriculture and other agricultural research 
institutes have played key roles in the popularization of 
agricultural technology. 
  Of the more than 300 items of scientific research 
achievements completed by the Shanxi Academy of Agricultural 
Sciences, 60 percent have been applied to farm production. For 
instance, research achievements in raising grain yield per 
hectare and enhancing crops' resistance to drought have been 
successfully applied. 
  The official said that to popularize scientific achievements 
in agriculture, the province has mobilized more than 10,000 
technicians to work in rural areas. 
  The province now has 200,000 hectares of high-yield fields 
for the application of new technology. 

</TEXT>

