<H3> <TI>   Liu Huaqing Meets With CIS Veterans' Delegation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Liu Huaqing Meets With CIS Veterans' Delegation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2205142994 Beijing XINHUA in English 1234 GMT 22 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2205142994 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, May 22 (XINHUA) -- Liu Huaqing, standing 
committee member of the Political Bureau of the Central 
Committee of the Communist Party of China, today met and had a 
cordial talk here with a joint delegation of veteran fighters 
from the Commonwealth of Independent States (CIS). 
  The delegation, with Chairman N. Vasilievich of the 
coordinating committee of the Veteran Fighters' Union of the CIS 
as its leader and Chairman M. Petrovich of the Veteran Fighters' 
Committee of Russia as its deputy leader, arrived here on May 20 
at the invitation of the National Committee of the Chinese 
People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC). 
  Liu, also vice-chairman of the Central Military Commission, 
said the veteran Chinese fighters have cherished a profound 
friendship with their counterparts of the CIS. 
  He noted that 1995 will celebrate the 50th anniversary of 
victory in the anti-fascist war, which he described as having 
historic significance not only to the people of the CIS, but 
also to the Chinese people. 
  "So we should hold celebrations on the occasion," he said. 
  During the meeting both Vasilievich and Petrovich shared the 
hope that the veteran fighters from the CIS should do their best 
to strengthen their friendly exchanges with their Chinese 
counterparts and push forward their friendship. 
  During the meeting, Liu also briefed the visitors on China's 
reform and opening to the outside world. 
  Hong Xuezhi, vice-chairman of the national committee of the 
CPPCC, participated in the meeting. 

</TEXT>

