<H3> <TI>   Leaders Express Condolences on Ito's Death </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Leaders Express Condolences on Ito's Death </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2005143694 Beijing XINHUA in English 1422 GMT 20 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2005143694 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, May 20 (XINHUA) -- Chinese President Jiang 
  Zemin and Premier Li Peng today sent messages of condolences 
to the bereaved family of Mr. Masayoshi Ito, a former Japanese 
foreign minister, who passed away this morning. 
  Qiao Shi, chairman of the Chinese National People's Congress 
Standing Committee, and Qian Qichen, vice premier and foreign 
minister, also sent similar messages to the bereaved family. 
  The messages spoke highly of Ito, former Japanese foreign 
minister of the Liberal Democratic Party government, hailing him 
as a Japanese statesman with political far-sight and an old 
friend respected and trusted by the Chinese people. 
  Ito had long dedicated himself to the cause of Sino-Japanese 
friendship and with firm conviction exerted positive efforts for 
the realization of normalizing Sino-Japanese relations and for 
the conclusion of a friendship treaty between the two countries, 
said the messages. 
  He also made outstanding contributions to the development of 
good-neighborly relations of friendship and cooperation between 
China and Japan. 
  The passing away of Ito is a big loss to the cause of Sino- 
Japanese friendship and the Chinese people will cherish his 
memory for ever, the messages added. 

</TEXT>

