<H3> <TI>   Cambodia's Khieu Samphan To Arrive in Beijing 25 May </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cambodia's Khieu Samphan To Arrive in Beijing 25 May </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2205111194 Beijing XINHUA in English 1047 GMT 22 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2205111194 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Phnom Penh, May 22 (XINHUA) -- Khieu Samphan, 
president of the Democratic Kampuchea Party (DKP) has been 
invited to attend a dinner hosted by King Norodom Sihanouk in 
Beijing on May 25. A representative of the DKP's president said 
here today. 
  The representative said that Khieu Samphan, who will be 
accompanied by a 6-member delegation, will go to the king's 
residence in Beijing immediately after his arrival in China's 
capital on May 25 on the way to attend a round-table meeting on 
peace and national reconciliation in Pyongyang. 
  The 71-year-old king proposed the convening of the 
round-table talks from May 27-30 at the royal residence of Chang 
So-on in the Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK) 
without any condition before he returned Beijing from Cambodia 
on May 18 for medical treatment. 
  The representative said that DKP supported the king's peace 
efforts and respected the people's hope on peace and rebuilding 
the country after 20-year-old war. It is a good thing to start 
talks on the peace between the royal government and the Khmer 
Rouge. 

</TEXT>

