<H3> <TI>   Meets Belgian National Bank Governor </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Meets Belgian National Bank Governor </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2105053994 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 1516 
GMT 19 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW2105053994 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Chinese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By reporter Kang Xinwen (1660 2450 2429)] </F>
  [Text] Brussels, 19 May (XINHUA) -- Visiting Li Ruihuan, 
chairman of the Chinese People's Political Consultative 
Conference [CPPCC] National Committee, met with Belgian National 
Bank Governor Verplaetse here today. They held cordial and 
friendly talks. 
  Verplaetse extended a warm welcome to Li Ruihuan's visit to 
Belgium, and enthusiastically commended China on its major 
achievements in reform and opening up. He said: China's rapid 
and sustained economic development has made China "a model of 
economic miracles in the Far East." 
  CPPCC Chairman Li Ruihuan indicated: Since carrying out 
reform and opening up, China has truly made satisfactory 
progress in developing its economy. However, it has also 
encountered some problems in the process. To resolve these 
problems, China needs to not only establish and improve laws and 
regulations and strengthen macroeconomic regulation and control, 
it also needs to improve qualities of all the Chinese people and 
to enhance all its nationalities' adaptability. 
  Li Ruihuan said: China is a country with a lot of people and 
it has a very arduous task to develop its economy. Therefore, 
while facing the need to import advanced Western technology and 
equipment, it also needs to learn from Western countries' 
experiences in regulating and controlling the market. He 
expressed the hope that Sino-Belgian bankers will increase 
bilateral exchanges and promote economic and trade cooperation 
between the two countries. 

</TEXT>

