<H3> <TI>   Li Ruihuan Departs Belgium for Home </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Li Ruihuan Departs Belgium for Home </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2305081394 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 1557 
GMT 21 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW2305081394 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Chinese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By reporter Kang Xinwen (1660 2450 2429)] </F>
  [Text] Brussels, 21 May (XINHUA) -- Li Ruihuan, chairman 
of the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference 
[CPPCC] National Committee, departed Brussels for home by 
special plane after successfully concluding a five-day official 
goodwill visit to Belgium today. 
  He was seen off at the airport by Hughes [name as received], 
second vice president of the Belgian Senate, and Chinese 
Ambassador to Belgium Ding Yuanhong. 
  Before boarding the plane, Chairman Li Ruihuan shook hands 
with and bid farewell to Vice President Hughes, thanking him for 
the kind invitation and warm reception. The latter 
congratulated Li Ruihuan on his successful visit. 
  Members of Li Ruihuan's entourage who returned in the same 
plane were Zhu Xun, secretary general of the CPPCC National 
Committee; Liu Feng, member of the CPPCC National Committee and 
chairman of the CPPCC Zhejiang Provincial Committee; Mei 
Xiangming, Standing Committee member of the CPPCC National 
Committee and vice chairman of the China Association for 
Promoting Democracy Central Committee; Jiang Enzhu, vice foreign 
minister; Wu Guanzhong, Standing Committee member of the CPPCC 
National Committee; Fang Fan, member of the CPPCC National 
Committee; and Tang Longbin, member and vice chairman of the 
Foreign Affairs Committee of the CPPCC National Committee. 
  Belgium was the fifth leg of Chairman Li Ruihuan's European 
tour. Prior to this, he had visited Finland, Sweden, Norway, and 
Denmark. During his stay in Belgium, he held talks with the 
principal leaders of the Belgian Parliament and Government on 
bilateral relations and international issues of mutual concern. 
He was also invited to visit Belgium's Chemistry Union, Bell 
Telephones Company, Antwerp drilling center, and other 
enterprises. 
  It has been learned that from the special plane, Li Ruihuan 
cabled a message to Belgian House of Representatives President 
Nothomb and Senate President Swaelen, expressing his heartfelt 
gratitude to the Belgian Parliament and Government for the warm 
hospitality accorded him during his stay in their country. He 
also asked them to convey appreciation to Prime Minister Dehaene 
and Vice Prime Minister and concurrently foreign minister Claes. 

</TEXT>

