  [Text] Brussels, May 21 (XINHUA) -- Li Ruihuan, chairman of 
the National Committee of the Chinese Peoples' Political 
Consultative Conference (CPPCC), ended his five-day goodwill 
visit to Belgium today. 
  Belgium is the last leg of Li's five-nation European tour 
which also took him to Finland, Sweden, Norway and Denmark. 
  Before departure for home, Zhu Xun, CPPCC secretary-general 
who accompanied Li during his five nation tour, described the 
visit as "successful." 
  The visit, the first of its kind by a CPPCC leader, has 
promoted understanding, exchanges and friendly cooperation 
between China and the five countries, Zhu said. 

