<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bonn, May 21 (XINHUA) -- A Chinese health delegation 
headed by Peng Peiyun, state councilor and minister in charge of 
the State Family Planning Commission, ended a week-long visit to 
Germany today. 
  During her visit, Peng held talks with Rita Suessmuth, 
president of the German Bundestag. They agreed that health 
specialists of the two countries, and all the people of China 
and Germany, should continue to develop cooperation and exchange. 
  Peng also met with German Minister of Health Horst Seehofer 
and Minister of Women and Youth Angela Merkel. 

