<H3> <TI>   Zhu Rongji Inspects Jiashan Shopping Center </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Zhu Rongji Inspects Jiashan Shopping Center </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2005115194 Hangzhou Zhejiang People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 1000 GMT 10 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW2005115194 </F>
<F P=104>  Hangzhou Zhejiang People's Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Mandarin </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Provincial News Hookup" program] </F>
  [Excerpt] On the afternoon of 26 April, colorful flags 
fluttered over the Jiashan Shopping Center, which won the 
glorious national title of 100-strong market for 1993. Inside, 
the atmosphere was warm. Inspecting the shopping center, Zhu 
Rongji, member of the Standing Committee of the CPC Central 
Committee Political Bureau and vice premier of the State 
Council, praised it saying it was beautifully built. 
  The Jiashan Shopping Center is situated in a location where 
Zhejiang, Jiangsu, and Shanghai meet. Being close to the 
Shanghai-Hangzhou railway and National Highway 320, it has 
become an important commodity distributing center in northern 
Zhejiang. The shopping center cost 15.93 million to build. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

