<H3> <TI>   Zou Jiahua Stresses Safety in Production </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Zou Jiahua Stresses Safety in Production </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2105210494 Beijing Central People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 2230 GMT 14 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW2105210494 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing Central People's Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Mandarin </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "News and Press Review" program] </F>
  [Text] The fourth safe production week campaign will be 
launched across the country from 15-22 May. Vice Premier Zou 
Jiahua called on leading cadres at various levels to set an 
example in treating it as an important task, so the safe 
production week campaign will be unfolded truly in an organized, 
well-guided, and down-to-earth way. 
  Zou Jiahua said: Since liberation, particularly during the 
more than 10 years since the start of reform and opening up, 
China has made great achievements in economic construction and 
rapid progress in ensuring safe production. However, the 
situation of safety in production remains grim and bad accidents 
have occurred frequently over the last two years. Those 
accidents have caused great losses to the people's lives and 
property. They have also hurt our country's reputation. For 
this reason, we must not treat the production safety issue 
lightly, and must pay great attention to it at all times. All 
enterprises should regard production safety as very urgent work 
and do it well. 
  Zou Jiahua emphasized: In launching the safe production week 
campaign, we must stress actual results and prevent formalism. 

</TEXT>

