<F P=100> Science &amp; Technology </F>
<H3> <TI>   Circular Urges Cadres To Learn Modern Science </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Circular Urges Cadres To Learn Modern Science </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2305071994 Beijing XINHUA in English 0655 GMT 23 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2305071994 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, May 23 (XINHUA) -- All members of the 
Communist Party of China (CPC) have been urged to study modern 
science and technology alongside the theory of building 
socialism with Chinese characteristics put forward by Deng 
Xiaoping and general knowledge on building a socialist market 
economy. 
  In today's world, the general office of the CPC Central 
Committee says in a circular publicized today, technology is 
developing rapidly and international competition in this field 
is growing ever more fierce. 
  "Under such circumstances," the circular says, "we will find 
ourselves in a passive condition if we hesitate to arm our party 
members and cadres with modern science and technology or improve 
the scientific and cultural level of the Chinese nation." 
  In studies, the circular says, special attention should be 
paid to the thesis "economic construction should rely on science 
and technology and scientific and technological work should 
serve economic construction" promulgated by Deng Xiaoping so as 
to shift the focus of economic construction and social 
development to technological advances and the improvement of the 
skills of workers. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-50817 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drchi099_l_94005" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-CHI-94-099 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  23 May 1994 </DATE1>

