<H3> <TI>   Zhejiang Attracts More Foreign Investment </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Zhejiang Attracts More Foreign Investment </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2205025594 Beijing XINHUA in English 0229 GMT 22 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2205025594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Hangzhou, May 22 (XINHUA) -- The daily improved 
investment conditions in Zhejiang Province, east China, are 
attracting an increasing number of foreign investors. 
  The province actually used foreign investment totalling 220 
million U.S. dollars in the first quarter of this year, an 
increase of about 70 percent over the same period last year. 
  Last year saw the province approve the establishment of 
4,400 
foreign-funded enterprises, involving a contractual investment 
of 3.7 billion U.S. dollars. Actual use of the investment 
amounted to 1.2 billion U.S. dollars. 
  A provincial official said that the growth was mainly 
fuelled 
by the better service of local government departments; the 
increase of direct foreign investment and construction of large 
infrastructure projects. 
  Once a project is approved, the government will follow its 
construction closely and is always ready to offer a helping 
hand, he added. 
  Of the contractual investment last year, about 300 million 
U.S. dollars came directly from enterprises solely funded by 
foreign investors. 
  More and more overseas investors have shown interest in 
energy development and transport projects in the province, the 
official noted. 

</TEXT>

