<H3> <TI>   New Economic Periodical Published in Guangdong </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    New Economic Periodical Published in Guangdong </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2105084194 Beijing XINHUA in English 0806 GMT 21 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2105084194 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Guangzhou, May 21 (XINHUA) -- A new periodical 
titled "Economy of Guangdong and Hong Kong" has recently come 
off press in south China's Guangdong Province. 
  With six issues per year, the periodical is published for 
industrial and commercial circles in Guangdong and Hong Kong. 
  It will carry the market-oriented policies formulated by the 
party and state as well as targets and measures adopted by 
Guangdong Province in its economic reform and economic 
development. 
  The periodical is also aimed at promoting the exchange of 
economic information between Guangdong and Hong Kong and Macao, 
and analyzing development trends and consumption tendencies in 
the three places. 
  Every issue of the periodical, which comprises 80 to 100 
pages, will be printed in the form of picture album. 
  Two deputy governors of Guangdong Province are advisors to 
the periodicals. 
  In the first issue of the periodical, there are columns such 
as economic forum, global trade, economic forecasts, commercial 
and business situation in Guangdong, and Hong Kong and Taiwan. 
  In the foreward to the periodical, Peng Shubao, director of 
the Guangdong Provincial Economic Commission, noted that at 
present, the relations between economic development trends in 
Guangdong and in Hong Kong and Macao are becoming increasingly 
closer. 
  The economic relations between guangdong, Hong Kong and 
Macao 
will produce an important impact on the economic expansion of 
the Asian-Pacific region in the next one or two decades, Peng 
said. 

</TEXT>

