<F P=100> Central-South Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   City in Hubei Punishes Corrupt District Cadres </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    City in Hubei Punishes Corrupt District Cadres </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   HK2205054594 Wuhan Hubei People's Radio Network in Mandarin 
1000 GMT 20 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK2205054594 </F>
<F P=104>  Wuhan Hubei People's Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Mandarin </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The city of Lichuan recently inflicted public 
punishments on a batch of leading cadres at and above the 
district deputy director level. These cadres were found to have 
accepted gifts and cash in violation of party and government 
discipline. 
  Over the past few years, some of Lichuan's party members and 
cadres fell into the habit of throwing banquets on such 
occasions as weddings, funerals, birthdays, housewarmings, and 
so on, at which they procured gifts and cash from guests. 
  Investigations show that by 10 March 1994, a total of 27 
leading cadres at and above the deputy district director level 
had been involved in such activities, including four cadres at 
the county deputy magistrate level, 16 cadres at the district 
director level, and seven cadres at the district deputy director 
level. While five cadres had each accepted more than 10,000 
yuan in cash from others, fifteen cadres, including four at the 
county magistrate level, had violated party and government 
discipline in these activities. 
  In view of this situation, the Lichuan City CPC Committee 
and 
Lichuan City People's Government recently decided to strictly 
enforce party and government discipline by meting out two 
inner-party disciplinary warnings and two administrative 
warnings to four cadres at the district director level and the 
district deputy director level, respectively; issuing a circular 
criticizing seven cadres at the district director level and the 
district deputy director level; and reporting the cases of four 
corrupt cadres at the county magistrate level to the relevant 
autonomous prefectural party committees and discipline 
inspection commissions for punishment in accordance with the 
relevant personnel management regulations. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

