BFN 

  [Text] Shenyang, May 22 (XINHUA) -- Wen Shizhen, 54, was 
appointed acting governor of northeast China's Liaoning Province 
today, to replace former governor Yue Qifeng. 
  The decision was made by the Eight Session of the Standing 
Committee of the Eighth Liaoning Provincial People's Congress, 
which also approved Yue's resignation as governor of Liaoning. 
  Yue was earlier named secretary of the Provincial Committee 
of the Chinese Communist Party (CPC) of Heilongjiang Province, 
also in northwest China. 
  Wen graduated from the machinery department of Dalian 
Engineering Institute in 1965. He has served as the deputy 
party secretary of the provincial committee of the CPC and 
deputy governor of the province. 

