<F P=106> [From the "Hookup" program] </F>
  [Text] Huang Kun-huei, chairman of the Mainland Affairs 
Council [MAC], Executive Yuan, pointed out yesterday [22 May] 
that in order to conclude the tasks related to dealing with the 
aftermath of the Qiandao Lake incident, Mainland China should 
respond quickly to the Strait Exchange Foundation [SEF] proposal 
made in early April for a special meeting between the SEF and 
the Association for Relations Across the Taiwan Straits [ARATS]. 
