long time, it will have an impact on arrangements for activities 
related to the Ku-Wang meeting. 
  Chairman Huang Kun-huei made these remarks when answering 
reporters' questions on whether MAC and SEF have started 
coordinating and having contact to push forward the second round 
of the Ku-Wang meeting. As for SEF chairman Ku Chen-fu and Vice 
Chairman Chiao Jen-he advocating to push forward the second 
Ku-Wang meeting based on the agreement on institutionalized 
contacts and talks between the two organizations, Chairman Huang 
Kun-huei said MAC and SEF have not yet discussed the issue. 

