<H3> <TI>   Former British Official on Hong Kong Issue, MFN </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Former British Official on Hong Kong Issue, MFN </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2105165394 Beijing XINHUA in English 1434 GMT 21 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2105165394 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Hong Kong, May 21 (XINHUA) -- Former British 
Foreign Secretary Geoffery Howe has said that the Sino-British 
joint declaration would still play a vital role in the transfer 
of power of Hong Kong in 1997. 
  Addressing an American Chamber of Commerce lunch here Friday 
[20 May] following his recent Beijing trip, Howe also said 
China's economic progress had given some assurance to the people 
of Hong Kong about their future. 
  Meanwhile, he warned that a decision by the United States to 
revoke China's most-favored nation (MFN) trading status would 
hit Hong Kong much heavier. "Curtailment of MFN status would 
provoke China as much as a bee-sting, and damage Hong Kong as 
much as a sledgehammer," he said. 

</TEXT>

