<H3> <TI>   Chinese Official Optimistic on Airport Financing </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chinese Official Optimistic on Airport Financing </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   HK2305072694 Hong Kong SOUTH CHINA MORNING POST in English 
23 May 94 p 2 </F>

<F P=103> HK2305072694 </F>
<F P=104>  Hong Kong SOUTH CHINA MORNING POST </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By Doreen Cheung in Beijing] </F>
  [Text] A senior Chinese official yesterday expressed 
optimism about the chances of reaching agreement on the 
financing of the new airport and its rail link. 
  Deputy Director of the State Council's Hong Kong and Macao 
Affairs Office Chen Ziying was replying to reporters who had 
suggested the Government's funding request from legislators for 
$820 million for the Chek Lap Kok airport railway might damage 
the talks. 
  "Things are moving on. Why are you so pessimistic?" he said. 
  Pro-China legislator Tam Yiu-chung said he believed the 
Airport Committee meeting on Friday had made some progress. 
  He did not think the funding request would hamper future 
talks. 
  "The airport projects have started. It is no longer a matter 
of whether to build it or not. 
  "The most important thing is the size of borrowings should 
not go beyond the $5 billion ceiling as laid down in the 
Memorandum of Understanding on the airport projects," he said. 

</TEXT>

