<H3> <TI>   12th Meeting on `Three Major Issues' Held in Macao </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    12th Meeting on `Three Major Issues' Held in Macao </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1905144894 Beijing XINHUA in English 1430 GMT 19 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1905144894 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Macao, May 19 (XINHUA) -- Members of the 
Sino-Portuguese Working Committee on the three major issues in 
the transitional period in Macao met here today for the 12th 
time to discuss and seek effective ways for the settlement of 
these issues. 
  Han Zhaokang, Chinese representative from the 
Sino-Portuguese 
Joint Liaison Group, told reporters after the meeting that the 
Chinese Government attaches equal importance to the settlement 
of the three major issues, namely the localization of public 
servants and law, as well as officialization of Chinese 
language, stressing that all of them are equally important to 
the smooth transition and transfer of power in Macao. 
  He pointed out that no matter the localization of public 
servants or the localization of law, language is a question that 
can not be ignored. So the three issues are of equal 
importance, he added. 

</TEXT>

