<F P=106> [By reporter Zeng Hu (2582 5706)] </F>
  [Text] Singapore, 19 May (XINHUA) -- Singapore Prime 
Minister Goh Chok Tong and Senior Minister Lee Kuan Yew today 
met separately with Chinese Vice Premier Li Lanqing. The two 
sides briefed each other and exchanged views on the Suzhou 
Industrial Park and other projects of mutual concern. 
  In the meeting with Li Lanqing, Goh Chok Tong related his 
recent trip to Germany and Britain, during which he briefed 
German and British businessmen about the Suzhou Industrial Park 
project, a Chinese-Singapore joint venture, and invited them to 
invest in China. 
  Li Lanqing expressed appreciation to the Singapore leader 
for 
making a trip to Europe to personally canvass investments for 
the Suzhou project. Li Lanqing briefed Goh about progress in 
carrying out the project. 
  In their meeting, Lee Kuan Yew and Li Lanqing held in-depth 
discussions on the project's personnel training and development 
plans. The two sides expressed satisfaction with the progress 
achieved in the project in little more than two months since the 
two governments signed the joint venture agreement. 
  Hu Ping, director of the State Council's Office on Special 
Economic Zones; Gan Ziyu, vice minister in charge of the State 
Planning Commission; and Chinese Ambassador to Singapore Yang 
Wenchang were present at the meetings. 

</TEXT>

